We first extract the key numbers from each statement.

Step 1. Return on Equity (ROE)  
• Net Profit (from income statement): 405,999.64  
• End Owner’s Equity (from balance sheet “Total Owner's Equity”): 28,405,999.64  
ROE = (Net Profit ÷ Owner’s Equity) × 100  
  = (405,999.64 ÷ 28,405,999.64) × 100 ≈ 1.43%

Step 2. Debt to Asset Ratio  
• Total Liabilities (from balance sheet “Total Current Liabilities”): 727,140.68  
• Total Assets (from balance sheet “Total Assets”): 29,133,140.32  
Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities ÷ Total Assets  
  = 727,140.68 ÷ 29,133,140.32 ≈ 0.025  
(When expressed to two decimal places, this rounds to 0.02.)

Step 3. Gross Profit Margin  
• Gross Profit (from income statement): 4,142,813.42  
• Total Revenue (from income statement “Total Revenue”): 14,542,813.42  
Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit ÷ Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (4,142,813.42 ÷ 14,542,813.42) × 100 ≈ 28.50%

Thus, the final answers are:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "1.43%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.02",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "28.50%"
  }
}
